  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Everyone's Favorite... T Rods.</span><hr size=1> I was thinking about T - Rods (about 20 mins before I level into 56... just typing while medding)   I don't know much about the high end raiding game, but I know that T Rods are a big part of it, and most mages really dont like spitting out thousands of them.  So I thought of something, that I think might work... but I figure I'll see what the other people think of it first... <br>
<br>
Here is the current version of rod of mystical transvergence...  At this point, I am going to ignore specialization completely...but that can be factored in later.<br>
Cost: 300Mana<br>
<br>
three charges of Mystical Transvergence <br>
Lose 300 HP for 220 mana<br>
<br>
<br>
Now here is what I think might work...<br>
Cost 500<br>
<br>
Unlimited charges of Linked Transvergence.<br>
Lose 300 HP, Gain 220 mana, Linked mage loses 100 mana the linked mage must have the mana for this to work.  <br>
<br>
This way, its the same net effect (minus that 500 to start with), only faster.  The linked mage must be in the group of the person with the rod.   <br>
<br>
Also,  A mage can click their Boots of blade calling or what ever, and not just have to pump out mod rods.<br>
<br>
What do you guys think about that?  I don't know how well this would work, but it would be alot less aggravating.  Feel free to shoot holes in this as necessary.<br>
<br>
~Nalila <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usenrye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senrye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 10:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1470.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res0n86l/avatars/LE12_av.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Everyone's Favorite... T Rods.</span><hr size=1> I think the fact that we wouldn't have control over our own mana pool makes the idea slightly flawed.<br>
