<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, yes and no.  You have to be in the group of the person you give the rod to.  If I give a rod to someone then leave the group.  That rod would be completely useless.  Even if another mage joined the group...  its linked to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> me</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> not to the mage in the group.    But also... you have to have some downside to the thing too...   I think there is a way to make the concept work, if not the coding.<br>
<br>
~Nalila <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usenrye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senrye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#333333>(8/11/02 11:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1470.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res0n86l/avatars/LE12_av.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Everyone's Favorite... T Rods.</span><hr size=1> The other problem is that in a lot of raiding situations, the cleric isn't always going to be in the same group as the mage.  Mages aren't needed in the &quot;Main Tank&quot; group, or in any particular group at multi-group raids.<br>
<br>
